comments.body:
> Should a CBOR version of application/csrattrs also be considered? That format had an issue that the semantics were not understood by most people and not clearly defined as well; see https://www.ietf.org/id/draft-ietf-lamps-rfc7030-csrattrs-07.html
> So not sure if that's something to stir into now.

@EskoDijk what is in your opinion the best way forward regarding `csrattrs`? Note that [draft-ietf-cose-cbor-encoded-cert-07](https://www.ietf.org/archive/id/draft-ietf-cose-cbor-encoded-cert-07.html#name-c509-attributes-registry) already specifies the CBOR versions of different attributes, so what remains to be done seems to be the specification of the high-level `csrattrs` structure. Does this belong to EST-oscore?

